                    <div class="artistes_description"><div class="description_wrapper"><p class="mono">Spanish-born Maloles Antignac divides her time between Paris and Madrid. Through the medium of sculpture, her work engages us to revisit our assumptions on feminity and our relationship with nature. A resident of the Martell Foundation in 2020, in 2018 Maloles Antignac took part in the creation of <em>Toguna</em>, an enduring collective work focused on the transmission of knowledge, at the Palais de Tokyo in Paris. The Gabrielle & Guillaume gallery devoted a solo show to her <em>Fertility</em> Cycle in 2019 under the curatorship of Marion Vignal. Her works have also been exhibited in Chile and Mexico. </p></div></div>
