                    <h6>Franklin Azzi</h6>
                    <div class="artistes_description"><div class="description_wrapper"><p class="mono">Born in 1975, architect Franklin Azzi lives and works in Paris. A graduate of the École Spéciale d’Architecture, he also studied in Scotland at the Glasgow School of Art. In 2006, he founded the Franklin Azzi Architecture Agency. A proponent of a pioneering cross-disciplinary approach mixing architecture, interior design, design and contemporary art, he conjures novel living and working spaces (The Bureau, Be In for LVMH), rethinking urban planning with careful consideration for legacy built areas (Beaupassage on behalf of Emerige) also devising dismountable and removable structures (the rooftop Pavilion at Galeries Lafayette). </p></div></div>
