                    <div class="artistes_description"><div class="description_wrapper"><p class="mono">Mathias Kiss is a French contemporary artist with Hungarian roots, born in Poissy near Paris in 1972. He lives and works in Paris. He reflects on the question of deconstruction of the classical legacy, bluring the borderlines between art and artesan, in the tradition of movements such as the Arts & Crafts or the Bauhaus school. His works featured at the Musée des Arts Décoratifs in 2016, and at the Palais des Beaux-Arts of Lille in 2019. In 2013, he was given the Wallpaper Design Award, then in 2016, the Young International Art Fair Brussels Award. He was president of the jury for the Grand Prix de la Création de la ville de Paris for 2020 – in the artistic crafts category.</p></div></div>
