                    <h6>Studio KO</h6>
                    <div class="artistes_description"><div class="description_wrapper"><p class="mono">Since they met at l’Ecole d’architecture des Beaux-Arts in Paris and the subsequent foundation of their own studio in 2000, Karl Fournier and Olivier Marty have displayed a singular signature on projects of all scales. Heirs to a rich vein of classical training, they lay claim to an immersive approach to their profession, encompassing architecture, interior design and furniture. Architects of the Yves-Saint-Laurent Museum in Marrakech, the Chiltern Firehouse hotel in London, instigators of the renovation of the Los Angeles landmark Château-Marmont, Studio KO devises bespoke furniture for each of its projects, a source of original experimentation, encounters with new textures, techniques and lighting.</p></div></div>
